{
    "level": "B2",
    "intro": "In this topic, you will learn <strong>Future Continuous Passive</strong> in detail. <strong>Important:</strong> this form is used very rarely in real communication due to its awkward construction.",
    "rules": [
        {
            "label": "Formula",
            "color": "emerald",
            "text": "<strong>Subject + will be being + V3</strong>:",
            "example": "The house will be being painted at this time tomorrow."
        },
        {
            "label": "Denial",
            "color": "rose",
            "text": "<strong>Subject + will not be being + V3</strong>:",
            "example": "The report will not be being written at that moment."
        },
        {
            "label": "⚠️ Attention",
            "color": "amber",
            "text": "This form is <strong>hardly used</strong>!",
            "example": "Краще: The house will be painted tomorrow."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "1. Structure of the Future Continuous Passive",
    "intro": "Formula: <strong>will + be + being + V3</strong>. This structure is inconvenient, so it is rarely used:",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "All persons",
            "title": "will be being + V3",
            "subtitle": "I/You/He/She/It/We/They will be being interviewed."
        },
        {
            "label": "Singular",
            "title": "will be being + V3",
            "subtitle": "The car will be repaired. - The car will be repaired."
        },
        {
            "label": "Plural",
            "title": "will be being + V3",
            "subtitle": "The documents will be processed. — The documents will be processed."
        },
        {
            "label": "⚠️ Rarely!",
            "title": "Better to avoid",
            "subtitle": "Usually replaced by Future Simple Passive."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "2. Affirmative sentences",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Structure",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "Word order: <strong>Subject + will be being + V3</strong>",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The house will be being painted at this time tomorrow.",
                    "ua": "The house will be being painted at this time tomorrow."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The project will be being discussed at 3 PM.",
                    "ua": "The project will be being discussed at 3 PM."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The documents will be being reviewed all day.",
                    "ua": "The documents will be being reviewed all day."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "⚠️ Practical advice",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "<strong>It is better to use the Future Simple Passive or the active state</strong>:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Instead: The house will be painted tomorrow.",
                    "ua": "Instead: The house will be painted tomorrow."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Or active: They will be painting the house.",
                    "ua": "Or active: They will be painting the house."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "3. When (in theory) to use the Future Continuous Passive?",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Continuous action in the future moment",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "To emphasize that an action will <strong>continue at a certain point</strong>:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "At 10 AM tomorrow, the meeting will be being held.",
                    "ua": "At 10 AM tomorrow, the meeting will be being held."
                },
                {
                    "en": "This time next week, the building will be being renovated.",
                    "ua": "This time next week, the building will be being renovated."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Why avoid this form?",
            "color": "rose",
            "description": "Reasons why this form is <strong>rarely used</strong>:",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Too awkward: \"will be being\" sounds clumsy.",
                    "ua": "Too awkward: \"will be being\" sounds clumsy."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Confusing: Three verb forms in a row (be being done).",
                    "ua": "Confusing: Three verb forms in a row (be being done)."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Easier alternatives exist.",
                    "ua": "Easier alternatives exist."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "4. Negative sentences",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Structure",
            "color": "rose",
            "description": "Add <strong>not</strong> after will: <strong>Subject + will not be being + V3</strong>",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The report will not be being written at that moment.",
                    "ua": "The report will not be being written at that moment."
                },
                {
                    "en": "The car will not be being repaired tomorrow afternoon.",
                    "ua": "The car will not be being repaired tomorrow afternoon."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Abbreviated form",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "Colloquial: <strong>won't be being</strong> (even more unusual)",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "The documents won't be being processed then.",
                    "ua": "The documents won't be being processed then."
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "5. Interrogative sentences",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Yes/No question",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "<strong>Will + Subject + be being + V3?</strong>",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "Will the house be being painted at that time?",
                    "ua": "Will the house be being painted at that time?"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Will the project be being discussed tomorrow?",
                    "ua": "Will the project be being discussed tomorrow?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Wh question",
            "color": "sky",
            "description": "<strong>Wh-word + will + Subject + be being + V3?</strong>",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "What will be being done at 5 PM?",
                    "ua": "What will be being done at 5 PM?"
                },
                {
                    "en": "Where will the meeting be being held?",
                    "ua": "Where will the meeting be being held?"
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "6. Better alternatives",
    "intro": "Instead of Future Continuous Passive, it is better to use:",
    "rows": [
        {
            "en": "❌ The house will be being painted.",
            "ua": "❌ The house will be being painted.",
            "note": "✅ The house will be painted. (Future Simple Passive)"
        },
        {
            "en": "❌ The report will be being written.",
            "ua": "❌ The report will be being written.",
            "note": "✅ They will be writing the report. (Future Continuous Active)"
        },
        {
            "en": "❌ The car will be being repaired.",
            "ua": "❌ The car will be being repaired.",
            "note": "✅ The car will be repaired. / The car is going to be repaired."
        }
    ],
    "warning": "📌 In 99% of cases, it is better to use Future Simple Passive or Future Continuous Active!"
}

{
    "title": "7. Active vs Passive у Future Continuous",
    "intro": "Comparison of active and passive state:",
    "rows": [
        {
            "en": "Active: They will be painting the house.",
            "ua": "Active: They will be painting the house.",
            "note": "→ Passive: The house will be being painted. (рідко)"
        },
        {
            "en": "Active: We will be discussing the project.",
            "ua": "Active: We will be discussing the project.",
            "note": "→ Passive: The project will be being discussed. (рідко)"
        },
        {
            "en": "Active: Someone will be repairing the car.",
            "ua": "Active: Someone will be repairing the car.",
            "note": "→ Passive: The car will be being repaired. (рідко)"
        }
    ],
    "warning": "📌 Future Continuous active state sounds much more natural!"
}

{
    "title": "8. Typical mistakes",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Error 1",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Skip being.",
            "wrong": "The house will be painted now. (якщо потрібен Continuous)",
            "right": "✅ The house will be being painted now. (або краще: is being painted)"
        },
        {
            "label": "Error 2",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "Wrong order.",
            "wrong": "The report will being be written.",
            "right": "✅ The report will be being written."
        },
        {
            "label": "Error 3",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "Using been instead of being.",
            "wrong": "The car will be been repaired.",
            "right": "✅ The car will be being repaired."
        },
        {
            "label": "Advice",
            "color": "emerald",
            "title": "A better strategy.",
            "wrong": "Намагатися використовувати Future Continuous Passive.",
            "right": "✅ Використовувати Future Simple Passive або Active."
        }
    ]
}
